This paper discusses the use of meta-learning for fairness in machine learning models. The primary focus is on optimizing models with minimal data, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also discusses fairness and bias in machine learning models, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
